Package aom.scripting.ui

Class SubMenu

Object
SubMenu
public class SubMenu
extends Object
Defines a SubMenu, a part of a MenuGadget. A SubMenu can have multiple other SubMenus as its children.
Author:
Mythic_Freak - mythic.freak[a]gmail.com

  • Field Details

    • children

      public List<SubMenu> children

    • consoleCommand

      public String consoleCommand
      Defines the command to be executed when the user clicks on this menu item. If no command is needed, set the field to null;

    • accelerator

      public String accelerator
      Defines the hotkey that can be used to jump to this entry. If no hotkey is needed, set the field to null;

    • configIndex

      public String configIndex
      This field provides a shortcut to make this menu's command act as the configToggle(string config) command. If no configIndex is needed, set the field to null;
      See Also:
      Config.configToggle(aom.scripting.datatypes.string)

    • disabled

      public boolean disabled
      Defines whether this menuitem is disabled or not.

    • separator

      public boolean separator
      Defines whether this menuitem acts as a separator or not. If this is true, no title will be shown, and no children should be added.

    • title

      public String title
      Defines the text that will be displayed on this menu item.
